name: Asparagus Tart with Prosciutto
author: Kate SR
summary: Puff pastry tart filled with creamy Swiss cheese, asparagus, and prosciutto makes a fabulous appetizer!
ingredients: 2 ounces prosciutto, cut into thin strips
1 pound asparagus spears, woody bases removed
directions: Thaw frozen puff pastry at room temperature for 20 minutes
Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper
Lightly flour a surface and roll pastry into a 10x16-inch rectangle
Place on the prepared baking sheet
Top with Swiss cheese, prosciutto, and asparagus tips, leaving a 1/2-inch border around the outside edge of the pastry sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until pastry is puffed and golden brown and asparagus is tender, 20 to 25 minutes
